  "text": "## Key Findings: Rust-Servo Shared Style System\n\n### Servo Style System Architecture\n\nContrary to the task's assumption, **Servo does NOT contain `components/style/` or `components/selectors/` directories**. Instead, Servo externally depends on the Stylo repository (https://github.com/servo/stylo) for CSS styling and selector parsing.\n\n**Servo's Root Cargo.toml (Workspace Dependencies):**\n- Line 160: `selectors = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- Line 178: `stylo = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- Line 169: `servo_arc = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- Line 179-183: Additional stylo-related crates (stylo_atoms, stylo_config, stylo_dom, stylo_malloc_size_of, stylo_traits) also from Stylo repository\n\n### Components Depending on Selectors in Servo\n\nMultiple Servo components depend on the external `selectors` crate:\n\n1. **components/layout/Cargo.toml** (Line 49)\n   - Dependencies: selectors, stylo, stylo_atoms, stylo_traits, and layout-related crates\n   - Path: components/layout/lib.rs\n\n2. **components/script/Cargo.toml** (Line 129)\n   - Dependencies: selectors, stylo, stylo_atoms, stylo_dom, stylo_malloc_size_of, stylo_traits\n   - Path: components/script/lib.rs\n\n3. **components/shared/layout/Cargo.toml** (Line 35)\n   - Named: layout_api\n   - Dependencies: selectors, stylo, stylo_traits\n   - Path: components/shared/layout/lib.rs\n\n4. **tests/unit/style/Cargo.toml** (Line 22)\n   - Named: style_tests\n   - Path: tests/unit/style/lib.rs\n   - Declares: `extern crate selectors;` (line 14) and `extern crate style;` (line 17)\n   - Dependencies: selectors, stylo, stylo_atoms, stylo_traits\n\n### Rust Compiler Integration with Servo/Stylo\n\n**src/tools/cargotest/main.rs** (Lines 73-82):\nRust's cargo test tool includes Servo as a test target:\n```rust\nTest {\n    name: \"servo\",\n    repo: \"https://github.com/servo/servo\",\n    sha: \"785a344e32db58d4e631fd3cae17fd1f29a721ab\",\n    lock: None,\n    // Only test Stylo a.k.a. Quantum CSS, the parts of Servo going into Firefox.\n    // This takes much less time to build than all of Servo and supports stable Rust.\n    packages: &[\"selectors\"],\n    features: None,\n    manifest_path: None,\n    filters: &[],\n}\n```\n\nThis confirms that the Rust compiler tests the `selectors` crate from Servo's Stylo dependency during its compatibility testing.\n\n### Proc_macro Bridge Definition (Rust Compiler)\n\nThe proc_macro bridge that Servo build scripts use is defined in the Rust standard library:\n\n**library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs** (Line 41)\n- Exports the `bridge` module with: `pub mod bridge;`\n- Located in: library/proc_macro/src/\n\n**library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs**\n- **Key Structure:** `BridgeConfig<'a>` (Line 154)\n  - Defines configuration for establishing active connection between proc_macro client (proc macro crate) and server (compiler front-end)\n  - Contains three fields:\n    - `input: Buffer` - Buffer used to pass initial input to the client\n    - `dispatch: closure::Closure<'a, Buffer, Buffer>` - Server-side function that the client uses to make requests\n    - `force_show_panics: bool` - Controls panic hook invocation\n  - Line 165-166: Explicitly implements `!Send` and `!Sync` for safety\n\n- **Macro System:** `with_api!` macro (Lines 48-104)\n  - Higher-order macro describing the server RPC API\n  - Generates type-safe Rust APIs for both client-side and server-side\n  - Defines FreeFunctions, TokenStream, Span, and Symbol API types\n\n**library/proc_macro/src/bridge/server.rs**\n- Implements server-side traits for the bridge\n- Defines `HandleStore<S: Types>` structure (Lines 14-25) for managing owned and interned handles\n- Uses macros `define_server_handles`, `Encode`, and `Decode` to implement serialization\n\n**library/proc_macro/src/bridge/client.rs**\n- Implements client-side bridge functionality\n- Defines local `Bridge` structure for TLS execution during macro expansion\n- Methods: `def_site()`, `call_site()`, `mixed_site()` for accessing global span information\n\n## Cross-Repository Dependency Chain\n\n**Rust Compiler → Standard Library → Proc_macro Bridge → Servo Crates**\n\n1. Rust's compiler uses the `library/proc_macro` crate to bridge between macro code and the compiler\n2. Servo components (layout, script) use the `selectors` and `stylo` crates from the external Stylo repository\n3. The Rust test suite includes Servo's selectors crate to ensure compatibility between the compiler and Stylo's CSS selector parsing implementation\n4. This architecture allows Servo (Firefox's rendering engine) to use Rust's proc_macro system while maintaining compatibility with Rust's standard library\n"", "structuredPatch": [], "originalFile": null}
